title: Crew Dragon Endurance set for return to Earth on Crew-5 mission
summary: The Crew-5 astronauts are preparing to return to Earth on the evening of Saturday, March 11, after spending the last five months aboard the International Space Station. Nicole Mann and Josh Cassada of NASA, Koichi Wakata of JAXA, and Anna Kikina of Roscosmos are preparing to undock their Crew Dragon, C210 Endurance, early on Saturday at 2:05 AM EST (07:05 UTC).

title: Canadian military orders space surveillance micro satellite
summary: Canada’s Department of National Defence is moving ahead with a new microsatellite project for space domain awareness.

title: Intelsat and Eutelsat forge multi-orbit capacity deal
summary: Eutelsat said March 9 it has signed a multi-million euro deal to provide more satellite capacity to Intelsat, including from OneWeb’s low Earth orbit network the French operator is acquiring.

title: Space sector reacts to collapse of Silicon Valley Bank
summary: Space companies and investors are reacting to the collapse of Silicon Valley Bank, a financial institution many relied on for investment, loans and traditional banking services.

title: Space Force allocates three historic Cape Canaveral launch pads to four companies
summary: The U.S. Space Force is allocating three launch complexes at Cape Canaveral, including one used for several NASA Mercury missions six decades ago, to four small launch vehicle startups as the service tries to keep up with growing launch demand.
